                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/483:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)<note n="20" xml:id="d268fn20">The same to the diplomatic representatives in
                                Great Britain (No. 316), Italy (No. 74), and Japan (No. 119) (861.77
                                Chinese Eastern/489, 490, 491).</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-27T12:00:00-05:00">November 27,
                                1929—noon</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>387. Department’s 384, November 26, 2 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d268fn21">See footnote 16, <ref target="#pg_350">p. 350</ref>.</note> I am
                            adding German Government. Inform Foreign Office.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
